ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC SGSCATTER < options>;  
      COMPARE X= variable | (variable-1 ... variable-n) Y= variable | (variable-1 ... variable-n)</options>;  
      MATRIX variable-1 < ... variable-n> </options>;  
      PLOT plot-request(s) </options>;  

The SGSCATTER procedure creates a paneled graph of scatter plots for multiple combinations 
of variables, depending on the plot statement that you use. You can use options to overlay 
fit plots and ellipses on your scatter plots.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: COMPARE X= variable | (variable-1 ... variable-n) 
      Y= variable | (variable-1 ... variable-n) </options>;

Creates a comparative panel of scatter plots with shared axes.
